        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3566551205" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4505945627366733616">It seems strange to say that I &quot;liked&quot; a book so filled with unpleasant characters doing nasty deeds, but I did. Larry Brown goes to some dark places, but his writing is so fine that you won&apos;t mind the journey into those unlit areas. He <i>knows</i> these rural denizens, driven by poverty and boredom to seek an escape, <i>any</i> escape from their lives of misery. <br/><br/>Brown instantly becomes one of those authors that makes you say, &quot;I gotta read <i>everything</i> by this guy!&quot;</span>
  <span id="freeText4505945627366733616" style="display:none">It seems strange to say that I "liked" a book so filled with unpleasant characters doing nasty deeds, but I did. Larry Brown goes to some dark places, but his writing is so fine that you won't mind the journey into those unlit areas. He <i>knows</i> these rural denizens, driven by poverty and boredom to seek an escape, <i>any</i> escape from their lives of misery. <br /><br />Brown instantly becomes one of those authors that makes you say, "I gotta read <i>everything</i> by this guy!"</span>
