        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3312791477" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16088827103547533694">Reading <i>Joe</i> is like living a whole other life. It’s gritty, rough, and exhausting. But oh, can Larry Brown write. Rural Mississippi is as much a character as all the hard-drinking men and the two main characters, young Gary Jones who finds a skewed but noble mentor in Joe Ransom. <br/><br/>This is my third Larry Brown book. I may wait until I’m feeling more grounded and energetic than I do right now to read another. <br/></span>

          </span>
        </div>


